<p>A business publishing 30 articles per month faces this math:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pure human:</strong> $2,400-$15,000/month</li>
<li><strong>Pure AI:</strong> $90-$450/month (plus editing time)</li>
<li><strong>AI-assisted hybrid:</strong> $750-$2,250/month</li>
</ul>
<p>That gap explains why 97% of content marketers now use AI in some capacity, according to <a href="https://contentmarketinginstitute.com/articles/ai-content-marketing-research/">research from the Content Marketing Institute</a>. The question is no longer whether to use AI. It is how much human oversight to apply.</p>
<h2>When to Use AI Writers</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Decision framework for AI vs human writers by content type" src="/images/blog/ai-vs-human-writers-decision-framework.webp" /></p>
<p>Use AI writers for these content types:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Product descriptions at scale</li>
<li>[ ] SEO meta descriptions and title tags</li>
<li>[ ] Social media post variations</li>
<li>[ ] FAQ pages and knowledge base articles</li>
<li>[ ] Data summaries and routine reports</li>
<li>[ ] Email subject line A/B test variations</li>
<li>[ ] First drafts for blog content</li>
<li>[ ] Internal documentation</li>
</ul>
<p>The common thread is structure. AI performs best when the format is predictable and the stakes are low. For guidance on scoring these outputs, see our <a href="/blog/content-scoring-guide/">content scoring guide</a>.</p>
<h2>When to Use Human Writers</h2>
<p>Use human writers for these content types:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] YMYL topics (health, finance, legal)</li>
<li>[ ] Thought leadership and opinion pieces</li>
<li>[ ] Brand storytelling and company narratives</li>
<li>[ ] Case studies with real customer data</li>
<li>[ ] Crisis communication</li>
<li>[ ] Content requiring original research or interviews</li>
<li>[ ] Regulated industry content</li>
<li>[ ] Flagship pillar pages</li>
</ul>
<p>The common thread is stakes. When accuracy, trust, or emotional connection determines success, human writers justify the higher cost. Learning <a href="/blog/write-blog-post-ranks/">how to write a blog post that ranks</a> still requires human editorial judgment.</p>
